parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake manifold gasket can cause coolant leaks, engine stalling, and overheating, leading to potential engine damage and accidents.
symptoms: knocking or unusual noises from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of engine valves and pistons can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and overheating, leading to potential engine damage and accidents.
The failure of the head gasket can cause coolant leaks, engine overheating, and loss of engine performance, leading to potential engine damage and accidents.

The failure of the transmission pressure control solenoid can cause the transmission to shift erratically, leading to vibrations, hard shifting, and grinding sounds, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The transmission shifting issues can cause the vehicle to surge or hesitate while shifting gears, leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle surges or hesitates while shifting gears
